Package org.androidtransfuse.annotations

Interface Summary
Labeled Declares an instance as having a unique String label.
ParcelConverter<T> Defines a concrete serialization of an instance to and from a Parcel.
 

Class Summary
Parcel.EmptyConverter Noop ParcelConverte used as a empty placeholder for the Parcel.value annotation parameter.
 

Enum Summary
ConfigChanges Constants representing the android:configChanges property on the Activity Manifest tag.
Exported Constants representing the android:exported property on the Activity Manifest tag.
IntentType Defines the different types of Intents available in the Android Manifest.
LaunchMode Constants representing the android:launchMode property on the Activity Manifest tag.
ScreenOrientation Constants representing the android:screenOrientation property on the Activity Manifest tag.
UIOptions Constants representing the android:uiOptions property on the Activity Manifest tag.
WindowSoftInputMode Constants representing the android:windowSoftInputMode property on the Activity Manifest tag.
 

Annotation Types Summary
Activity Defines a class to be a Transfuse Activity component.
Application Defines a class to be a Transfuse Application component.
Asynchronous AOP method interceptor annotation which executes the annotated method on a new Thread.
Bind On a @TransfuseModule class, defining a binding with @Bind defines a relationship between two related classes in which for each given type the class bound to will be used during injection.
Bindings Allows for multiple @Bind bindings to be provided on a @TransfuseModule class.
BindInterceptor On a @TransfuseModule class, specifying a @BindInterceptor associates an interceptor annotation to the MethodInterceptor implementation.
BindInterceptors Allows for multiple @BindInterceptor declarations to be provided on a @TransfuseModule class.
BindProvider On a @TransfuseModule class, defining a Provider binding with @BindProvider defines a relationship between a class and a Provider.
BindProviders Allows for multiple @BindProvider declarations to be provided on a @TransfuseModule class.
BroadcastReceiver Defines a class to be a Transfuse Broadcast Receiver component.
ContextScope Defines the scope of the annotated Type or @Provides type to be a Context-Scoped object.
Extra Injection qualifier annotation specifying the injection should be drawn from the Bundle Extras by extra name.
Fragment Defines a class to be a Transfuse Fragment component.
Injector Defines an interface as a Transfuse Injector.
Intent The annotation representation of the Android Manifest Intent XML tag.
IntentFilter The annotation representation of the Android Manifest IntentFilter tag.
IntentFilters Allows for multiple @IntentFilters to be defined on a class.
Layout Used in conjunction with the @Activity annotation, defines the layout resource to use.
LayoutHandler Used in conjunction with the @Activity annotation, defines a LayoutHandlerDelegate to use to generate the view setup code.
MetaData The annotation representation of the Android Manifest MetaData XML tag.
MetaDataSet Allows for multiple MetaData annotations to be used on a single Transfuse Component.
NonConfigurationInstance Defines the annotated field to be serialized using the Activity.onSaveNonConfigurationInstance() method and deserialized using the Activity.onCreate() method.
Observes Defines a method to observe an event triggered via the EventManager class when registered.
OnActivityCreated Activity onActivityCreated() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnBackPressed Activity onBackPressed() callback method annotation.
OnConfigurationChanged Activity, Service and Fragment onConfigurationChanged() callback method annotation.
OnCreate Activity, Service, Application and Fragment onCreate() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnDestroy Activity and Fragment onDestroy() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnDestroyView Fragment onDestroyView() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnDetach Fragment onDetach() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnListItemClick ListActivity onListItemClick() callback method annotation.
OnLowMemory Application onLowMemory() callback method annotation.
OnPause Activity and Fragment onPause() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnRebind Service onRebind() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnReceive BroadcastReceiver onReceive() callback method annotation.
OnRestart Activity onRestart() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnRestoreInstanceState Activity onRestoreInstanceState() callback method annotation.
OnResume Activity and Fragment onResume() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnSaveInstanceState Activity onSaveInstanceState() callback method annotation.
OnStart Activity onStart() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnStop Activity onStop() Lifecycle Event callback method annotation.
OnTaskRemoved Service onTaskRemoved() callback method annotation.
OnTerminate Application onTerminate() callback method annotation.
OnTrimMemory Application onTrimMemory() callback method annotation.
Parcel Identifies a class to be wrapped by a Parcelable wrapper.
Preference Injection qualifier annotation specifying a preference to be injected by name.
Provides Configures a factory method to provide an instance of the return type for injection in a @TransfuseManifest annotated configuration and binds it to the return type.
RegisterListener Specifies the given type, field or method return type as a listener to the identified component.
Resource Injection qualifier annotation specifying which Android Resource to inject.
Service Defines a class to be a Transfuse Service component.
SystemService Injection qualifier annotation to specify which System Service to inject by name.
TransfuseModule Defines a configuration module for Transfuse.
Transient Defines the annotated getter or setter property as ignored when generating a Parcel converter.
UIThread AOP method interceptor annotation which executes the annotated method within a Handler.post() call.
View Injection qualifier annotation specifying which view is injected by resource id or tag.
